One community, two shop owners from different parts of the continent. Both of them desperately trying to claim a sizeable piece of the spaza-shop cake. eNCA contributor Mpho Lakaje has more. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - What does the future of foreign shop owners look like? Will they continue running their small businesses in South Africa’s townships? READ: Foreign-owned spaza shops on Cape Flats feel threatened Or will they have to shut down and give way to their local counterparts? Earlier this year, government revealed it’s looking to introduce maximum quotas on the number of documented foreign nationals with work visas. READ: Spaza shops: how regulatory avoidance harms informal workers If adopted as law, this could make it impossible for foreign nationals to own and run spaza shops. It comes as tensions between immigrants and local entrepreneurs reach boiling point. * eNCA contributor Mpho Lakaje reports.